definitions.definition: A male given name from Old French from the Norman French for Edward
A surname transferred from the given name .
A locality , formerly a settlement, in the Rural Municipality of Pipestone , Manitoba , Canada , named after J. S. Ewart .
A civil parish (without a council) north-west of Wooler , north Northumberland , England .
